Purchase options and add-ons

  • SINGLE 12 INCH SEALED WEDGE SHAPED SUBWOOFER ENCLOSURE: The Bbox 12 inch single sealed wedge shape SPL-Tuned subwoofer box enclosure is designed for optimum bass response and low frequency reproduction which is ideal for lower profile sound quality subwoofers. Get the most out of your vehicle's subwoofer with car stuff designed for power and quality.
  • SPECIAL FORMULA: We use Aliphatic wood glue on our 12" subwoofer enclosures to ensure an airtight seal between all MDF parts. Each 12 inch subwoofer box also gets a second application of glue around all internal joints after the final assembly.
  • HIGH GRADE MDF: Our subwoofer box enclosures are built with a durable MDF that is 1" thick for solid frequency response and accurate music reproduction and we use a CNC Miter to ensure an airtight fit for your powered subwoofer. Our Dado design and construction offers a precision fit for our car subwoofer boxes & enclosures, which ensures a rattle and noise free environment.
  • AIRTIGHT RECESSED SIDE PANELS: We use quality materials like our special aliphatic resin wood glue and brad nails from a pneumatic nail gun to create a tight hold on the MDF parts during the glue drying process to ensure that our subwoofer boxes have an airtight no-leak, no-rattle air chamber improving the overall sound quality of your sound system
  • BETTER SOUND, BETTER BASS, BETTER FUN: Get the party started with sound quality you can truly jam to. Our subwoofer enclosures turn your truck into a music machine! Dramatically improve the sound quality and bass response of your truck’s audio system and listen to the music the way it was meant to be heard!

What's in the box

  • Item

    • From the manufacturer

    Introducing the Bbox Line of Products

    Designed and engineered in the USA, the Bbox line of enclosures are manufactured and imported from overseas to provide an economical solution to all of our customer's needs.


    Image on the left shows our Miter Edge Construction versus a traditional end/butt joint on the right

    Using Atrend's excellent woodworking techniques and design, combined with oversees manufacturing, allows BBox to be the best economical solution for our budget-minded clients.

    More Than Just A Box

    Miter & Dado Construction

    All of our Atrend and Bbox subwoofer enclosures are engineered and constructed to be the strongest on the market. Our outside panels feature our signature Miter and Dado construction, which adds extra reinforcement and structural integrity to our subwoofer enclosures. Ultimately, these construction techniques provide unsurpassed build and sound quality in Bbox enclosures.

    • Mitered Edge Construction Provides A Cleaner Finish and a Tighter Seal
    • Miter Joints Feature Over 41% More Surface Area Compared to a Traditional Butt Joint
    • More Surface Area Translates Into A Stronger Bond

    Image on the left shows our Dado Reinforcement versus a traditional end/butt joint on the right.

    Using these techniques provides unsurpassed fitment and build quality.

    • Dado Joints Offer An 80% Increase in Surface Area Compared to Traditional Butt Joints
    • Unsurpassed Shear Strength To Withstand Even The Hardest Hitting Subwoofers
    • Precise, High Quality Fit and Finish

    Attention to Detail

    3/4" MDF Front Baffle

    Select Bbox enclosures feature a 3/4" thick MDF front baffle to reduce panel flex and provide a solid mounting surface for unsurpassed sound quality.

    3/4" MDF Construction

    Bbox enclosures by Atrend feature high-quality 3/4" MDF panels to withstand the deepest bass.

    Atrend's Trick Glue

    Our Bbox enclosures are built using Atrend's special blend of Trick Glue for up to 3600 PSI of holding ability while maintaining a flexible and durable seal.

    Premium Charcoal Carpet

    Bbox features Atrend's Premium Charcoal Carpet to match the interior of most vehicles.

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    4.0 out of 5 stars Very Good Box for 2002 Chevy 2500HD Crew Cab
    Reviewed in the United States on February 17, 2013
    Size: 12"Style: SINGLE SEALEDVerified Purchase
    Well when I ordered these, they said they fit my vehicle. Yes they will but with quite a bit of modifications to your rear seat area. I have a 2002 2500HD LT Crew Cab. I installed these behind the rear seat. Since it is a LT version it may have extra trim pieces that non-LT models may have. My truck has cloth covered panels that seal the gap when you flip the back seat down / forward. These have to go first. Second, the metal bracket that these trim pieces screw to have to be cut out. I used an angle grinder with a cut off wheel. Next, the carpet padding behind the seat ledge where the speakers will sit needs to be cut out otherwise the cabinets won't sit low enough and the rear seat will hit the speakers when they are in their upright normal driving position. My truck also has a cloth covered piece of heavy insulated covering that goes across the rear of the cab, this has to go also to get the room you need. I have them installed and they fit great now and they look fine given the trim pieces I had to remove. With the seats upright in the normal position you cannot see any of the panels I had to remove. Originally I order two of the Kicker CompVR 07CVR124 12-Inch 4-Ohm DVC Subwoofers.
    I ended up returning them going for a more shallow pair, MB Quart Reference RLP304 12-Inch Flat Woofer 600-Watt Maxx 300-Watt RMS. The first set of Kicker's wouldn't sit flush in the boxes as the magnet was about 1/2" too deep. Again, when I selected the boxes on Amazon it automatically recommended the Kicker Sub's saying the would fit but they didn't

    Lastly, I ordered the MB Quart ONX1.1000D D-Class Amplifier to power these two subs. Plenty of power to drive these two speakers. I did also add some Polyfil insulation to each box to fool the speakers into thinking the boxes are actually bigger than they are. If you do not understand how this works by adding Polyfill, Google it. It is a common trick than professional installers will use on small boxes.

    Overall, I am extremely happy with my setup and overall look. I took my time to make is fit right and look clean and no sloppy edges showing. The only reason I gave these boxes a 4 star and not 5 is because they do not drop in and fit as described. You really need to have some skills to modify your truck but the end result will be a great fit. Of course a 10" sub would fit very easily in this crew cab but I really wanted to go for the 12" so I kind of knew I would be in for some modifications. Be Patient and take your time and the results will come out great.

My truck has cloth covered panels that seal the gap when you flip the back seat down / forward. These have to go first. Second, the metal bracket that these trim pieces screw to have to be cut out. I used an angle grinder with a cut off wheel. Next, the carpet padding behind the seat ledge where the speakers will sit needs to be cut out otherwise the cabinets won't sit low enough and the rear seat will hit the speakers when they are in their upright normal driving position. My truck also has a cloth covered piece of heavy insulated covering that goes across the rear of the cab, this has to go also to get the room you need. I have them installed and they fit great now and they look fine given the trim pieces I had to remove. With the seats upright in the normal position you cannot see any of the panels I had to remove. Originally I order two of the Kicker CompVR 07CVR124 12-Inch 4-Ohm DVC Subwoofers.
    I ended up returning them going for a more shallow pair, MB Quart Reference RLP304 12-Inch Flat Woofer 600-Watt Maxx 300-Watt RMS. The first set of Kicker's wouldn't sit flush in the boxes as the magnet was about 1/2" too deep. Again, when I selected the boxes on Amazon it automatically recommended the Kicker Sub's saying the would fit but they didn't

    Lastly, I ordered the MB Quart ONX1.1000D D-Class Amplifier to power these two subs. Plenty of power to drive these two speakers. I did also add some Polyfil insulation to each box to fool the speakers into thinking the boxes are actually bigger than they are. If you do not understand how this works by adding Polyfill, Google it. It is a common trick than professional installers will use on small boxes.

    Overall, I am extremely happy with my setup and overall look. I took my time to make is fit right and look clean and no sloppy edges showing. The only reason I gave these boxes a 4 star and not 5 is because they do not drop in and fit as described. You really need to have some skills to modify your truck but the end result will be a great fit. Of course a 10" sub would fit very easily in this crew cab but I really wanted to go for the 12" so I kind of knew I would be in for some modifications. Be Patient and take your time and the results will come out great.
